My God is an-y hour SO sweet, From blush of morn to evening star, As that which calls me to thy feet, The hour of prayer. Blest is the tranquil hour of morn, And blest that solemn hour of eve, When on the wings of prayer upborne, The world I leave. Copyright 1892, by C. C. What peace of mind ! Then is my strength by thee renewed ; Lord till I reach yon blissful shore, Then are my sins by thee forgiven, No privilege SO dear shall be Then dost thou cheer my solitude As thus my inmost soul to pour With hopes of heaven.
